To all vets,<br><br>
Also, forgot to mention that the youngest helicopter pilot to get killed was WO1 Raymond Howard Chase Jr.  He was born on 13 Aug 1948 and died on 10 Nov 1967 at 7,028 days old or 19.3 years.  I'm speaking to any helicopter pilots or crews here, How old were you when you flew in Vietnam?<br><br>
One of the guys my family knew that was killed was a Medivac helicopter pilot, one of those guys with the big red crosses on his Huey.  He was still shot down anyway.  Did the medivac's get targeted on purpose, or was it that Charlie shot at anything in the air?  I heard that medivacs were purposely not heavily armed in order to comply with Geneva Convention, is that true as well?<br>

